problem:
According to the table below, how many dollars are in the median value of the 59 salaries paid to this company's employees?

\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|}
\hline
\textbf{Position Title}&\textbf{\# with Title}&\textbf{Salary}\\\hline
President&1&$\$130{,}000$\\\hline
Vice-President&5&$\$90{,}000$\\\hline
Director&10&$\$75{,}000$\\\hline
Associate Director&6&$\$50{,}000$\\\hline
Administrative Specialist&37&$\$23{,}000$\\\hline
\end{tabular}
solution: Since more than half the employees are Administrative Specialists, the median salary will be an administrative specialist, thus, $\boxed{\$23{,}000}$.
model_solution:
To find the median salary, we first need to determine the total number of employees. The given table provides this information, which is 59 employees. 

Since there are 59 employees, the middle value is the 30th employee when the salaries are listed in order from lowest to highest. 

Starting from the lowest paid employees, the first 37 employees are Administrative Specialists with a salary of $\$23{,}000$. 

This means the 30th employee is also an Administrative Specialist with a salary of $\$23{,}000$.

Therefore, the median value of the salaries is $\boxed{\$23{,}000}$.
